title: A Pictorial history of Crime (History Society).pdf
description:
Crown | 1966 | Pdf | Eng | 288 pages | 44.5 MB | ISBN-10: 0517095939

A pictorial history of crime - from 1840 to the Present

heavily illustrated with b/w photos

Here are the stories of the Snyder murder, the Lindbergh kidnaping, the Brink robbery, the great British train robbery, the notorious outlaws Ned Kelly and Jesse James, the unholy swindlers Horation Bottomley, Jabez Balfour, Ivar Kreuger, and Philip Musica who invented a completely non-existent company with which his own respectable drug firm had enormous dealings, and hundreds of similar cases
